quran[47]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Say: It is communicated to me that a party of the jinn heard (the Quran) and said, “We have heard a wonderful Quran"
  72,2,"It guides to the right way, so we have believed in it and we will never associate any partner with our Lord"
  72,3,"And Exalted be the Majesty of our Lord, He has not taken a wife or a son"
  72,4,And the foolish among us used to say unjust (things) about God
  72,5,And we thought that mankind and jinn never speak a lie against God
  72,6,And persons from among human beings used to seek protection of persons from among the jinn so they increased them in error
  72,7,And they (too) thought as you thought that God will never raise anyone (to life after death)
  72,8,And we searched the sky but found it filled with strong guards and flames
  72,9,"And we used to sit in some of the sitting places thereof to hear, but now whoever hears, he finds a flame waiting for him"
  72,10,And we do not know whether evil is intended for those who are in the earth or their Lord intends (to guide) them to the right way
  72,11,"And among us are those who are righteous and among us (are those who are) other than that, we are sects following different traditions"
  72,12,And we know that we can neither defeat God in the earth nor can we defeat Him by flight
  72,13,"And when we heard the guidance, we believed in it, so whoever believes in his Lord, he should neither fear loss nor error"
  72,14,And among us are those who have submitted (as Muslims) and among us are those who are unjust. So those who have submitted (as Muslims) such have taken to the right way
  72,15,"And as for those who are unjust, they are the fuel for hell.”"
  72,16,And if they establish (themselves) on (the right) tradition We would give them to drink abundant water
  72,17,"so that We may test them thereby, and whoever turns away from the remembrance of his Lord He will cause him to enter severe punishment"
  72,18,And the mosques are God's so do not pray to anyone (else along) with God
  72,19,And when the servant of God stood up to pray to Him they almost crowded over him
  72,20,"Say, “I pray only to my Lord and I do not associate anyone with Him.”"
  72,21,"Say, “I certainly do not control for you anything, wrong or right.”"
  72,22,"Say, “None can ever protect me against God and I can never find besides Him, (any source of) refuge"
  72,23,"(my duty is nothing) but to convey (the communications) from God and His messages, and whoever disobeys God and His messenger, then for such, there is certainly the fire , of hell, in which they will stay forever.” which they will stay forever.”"
  72,24,"(The disbelievers will not believe) till (the time) when they see that which they are promised, then they will know who is weaker in helpers and lesser in number"
  72,25,"Say, “I do not know whether that which you are promised is nearer or whether my Lord has made its (time of happening) far off.”"
  72,26,"Knower of the unseen, but He does not reveal His unseen to anyone"
  72,27,"except to a messenger whom He chooses, but He makes one who is watchful, to move before him and behind him"
  72,28,that He may know (mark out) that they have indeed conveyed the messages of their Lord. And He encompasses all that is with them and He computes the number of everything
  73,1,O you who are wrapped up in garments
  73,2,Rise (to pray in) the night except a little
  73,3,half of it or a little less than that
  73,4,or increase it and recite the Quran gradually (giving) intervals
  73,5,We will put on you (the responsibility of delivering) a weighty statement
  73,6,The rising at night (for righteous work) certainly gives rise to more strength of co-ordination and firmly established speech (because)
  73,7,during the day you certainly have prolonged occupation
  73,8,And remember the name of your Lord and devote yourself to Him (with exclusive) devotion
  73,9,"Lord of the east and the west, there is no god except Him, so take Him as a Trustee"
  73,10,And be patient on what they say and keep away from them in a good (manner of) keeping away
  73,11,"And leave Me and the deniers, the possessors of favours (from Me) and give them a little time"
  73,12,"Certainly, with Us are heavy fetters and hell fire"
  73,13,and a food that chokes and a painful punishment
  73,14,"The day the earth will quake and the mountains (too), and the mountains will become a heap of running sand"
  73,15,"We have sent to you a messenger, a witness over you, as We had sent a messenger to Pharaoh"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the messenger, so We seized him with a severe seizure"
  73,17,"If you reject, then how will you guard (yourselves) on the day which will make children grey headed"
  73,18,(and) on which (day) the sky will be cleft asunder ? His promise is to be fulfilled
  73,19,"This is certainly a reminder, so whoever wills, let him take a way towards his Lord"